FBIS4-63539 "drsov099_a_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Yeltsin Warns Kravchuk Not To Use Force in Crimea Yeltsin Warns Kravchuk Not To Use Force in Crimea LD2005175994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1700 GMT 20 May 94 LD2005175994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] Today, Russian President Boris Yeltsin answered journalists' questions about the situation in Crimea: [Begin Yeltsin recording] I spoke with President Kravchuk of Ukraine yesterday. We discussed these issues. I gave a warning and he promised that Ukraine will not use any force whatsoever in Crimea. He promised me this, and we hope that the president, a respectable person, will keep his promise. [end recording]
